Description: Fix delete/delete[] mismatches (64-bit portability)
 Arrays allocated with new[] must be freed with delete[]. Using plain
 delete on an array pointer is undefined behaviour and can cause heap
 corruption, especially visible on 64-bit architectures where allocator
 metadata layout differs from 32-bit.
 .
 Affected arrays in idscroller.cc: LongString, tmp, linea.
 Affected arrays in flubber.h: Buffer, lut, zbuffer.
Generated-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
Reviewed-by: Nicolas HOUDELOT <nicolas@demosdebs.org>
Applied-Upstream: no
